EMPLOYEE LEAVE POLICY
Purpose: This policy provides guidelines for annual leave, sick leave, maternity leave, and emergency leave for employees of Challenge Enterprises of Ghana. Annual Leave: Employees are entitled to 21 working days of annual leave per year, subject to approval by their supervisor. Sick Leave: Employees who are unable to work due to illness must notify their supervisor
and may be required to provide a medical certificate. Maternity Leave: Eligible employees are entitled to maternity leave in accordance with
Ghanaian labour regulations. Leave Application Procedure: Employees must submit leave requests through the
SmartConnect platform at least two weeks before the intended leave date. Responsibilities: Managers are responsible for approving leave requests and ensuring
adequate departmental coverage.
